N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1ยง 8.5 - Limitations on use of identification stamps or stencils

State Regulations

No identification stamp or stencil as provided pursuant
to this Part shall be used to mark cheese other than cheddar, washed curd, or
colby cheese which conforms to the standards for such cheese pursuant to
subdivisions 29, 30 and 31 of section
46
of the Agriculture and Markets Law. Notes
